results.name: Decimal expansion of B, the coefficient of n*log(n)^2 in the asymptotic formula of Ramanujan for Sum_{k=1..n} (d(k)^2), where d(k) is the number of distinct divisors of k.
comment: The coefficient of n*log(n)^3 in the same asymptotic formula is A = 1/Pi^2.
reference: Steven R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge University Press, 2003, Section Sierpinski's Constant, p. 124.
link: Adrian W. Dudek, An Elementary Proof of an Asymptotic Formula of Ramanujan, arXiv:1401.1514 [math.NT], 2014.
Ramanujan's Papers, Some formulas in the analytic theory of numbers Messenger of Mathematics, XLV, 1916, 81-84, Formula (3).
